// SessionStatusPanel
// Shows current collab session phase, last activity time, current item, and progress bar.
// Supports two layout variants: default (stacked, for sidebar) and inline (horizontal, for header).
// Returns nothing if no collabState is available.

Phase color is determined by the session state string (e.g., brainstorm = blue,
execute-batch = green, systematic-debugging = red, vibe-active = pink).
Progress bar is shown when task or item progress data is available:
- Execution phases show task completion (completed / total tasks).
- Brainstorming/rough-draft phases show item documentation progress.

FUNCTION formatRelativeTime(isoString) -> string
  Converts an ISO timestamp to a relative time string (e.g., "5m ago", "2h ago", "3d ago").
  Returns "just now" for timestamps under 60 seconds ago.

---

FUNCTION getPhaseColor(state, displayName) -> string
  Returns Tailwind color classes for the phase badge.
  Matches on state prefix/value first (brainstorm, rough-draft, execute-batch, etc.).
  Falls back to matching keywords in displayName if state is not set.
  Returns gray classes as default.

---

FUNCTION SessionStatusPanel(props) -> ReactNode                           EXPORT
  CALLS: useSessionStore (sessionStore)
  Reads collabState from sessionStore. Returns null if absent.
  Computes progress values from completedTasks/pendingTasks (execution) or documentedItems/totalItems (brainstorming).
  IF variant is "inline": renders phase badge, relative timestamp, current item, and compact progress bar horizontally.
  IF variant is "default": renders phase badge, relative timestamp, current item in a row, followed by a full-width progress bar below.
